cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE

This paper is about learning to rank in e-commerce search engines, which is a problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel policy gradient algorithm for learning an optimal ranking policy, which is a type of reinforcement learning (RL) and falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the properties of a search session Markov decision process (SSMDP), which is a type of decision-making problem and can be categorized under the sub-categories of data structures (DS) and software engineering (SE).
